    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Palestinian Summer: The Wrong Games</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Peter G Hill letter deplores military-style camps for Palestinian children described in Aug 3 article</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Palestinian Summer Camp Offers the Games of War'' (front page, Aug. 3):</p>
        <p>To send teenagers to camp to learn destructive behavior is an abomination. Yasir Arafat, the Palestinian leader, should call an immediate halt to this practice and change the camps from military-style camps to camps that teach teenagers life and social skills that will benefit them and their society.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Palestinian Summer Camp Offers the Games of War'' (front page, Aug. 3):</p>
        <p>To send teenagers to camp to learn destructive behavior is an abomination. Yasir Arafat, the Palestinian leader, should call an immediate halt to this practice and change the camps from military-style camps to camps that teach teenagers life and social skills that will benefit them and their society.</p>
        <p>Swimming, tennis, arts and crafts, computer and writing skills are more important than aggression toward a society you are trying to make peace with. An immediate change of camp life and philosophy would send a positive message to the world.</p>
        <p>PETER G. HILL  Weston, Mass., Aug. 3, 2000</p>
      </block>
